  "response": "The English word that best captures the meaning of \"antaryami\" is **omnipresent**.\n\nHere's why, and some other options with nuances:\n\n*   **Omnipresent:** This literally means \"present everywhere.\" \"Antaryami\" refers to a being or power that resides within everything and everyone, knowing all and being present in all aspects of existence. This is the closest single-word translation.\n\nHere are some other terms, and why they might also apply, but aren't quite as encompassing:\n\n*   **Inner witness:** (This is a common interpretation). The \"Antaryami\" is the one who observes all actions and thoughts from within.\n*   **Indwelling spirit:** This emphasizes the presence of a divine entity *inside* something or someone.\n*   **Inner controller:** This emphasizes the aspect of the Antaryami as the one who guides or influences from within.\n*   **Immanent:** This describes something existing or operating within; inherent. (While correct, it lacks the personal agency that \"Antaryami\" suggests).\n\n**In conclusion:**\n\nWhile \"inner witness,\" \"indwelling spirit,\" or \"inner controller\" highlight specific aspects, **\"omnipresent\"** is the most comprehensive single-word English translation of \"antaryami\" because it best conveys the idea of a being present everywhere and within everything.",
